Subject: Worker Lanes

Description: SOP contract for local and remote-capable worker lanes in a turn spool.

& [WorkerLaneSet] is the set of supported worker lanes
  + [local_gpu] is a local GPU-backed inference lane through an available configured local provider
  + [lm_studio_cli] is a local LM Studio OpenAI-compatible worker lane
  + [openai_codex] is an OpenAI Codex hosted agent lane
  + [codex_cli] is an OpenAI Codex CLI worker lane and preferred operational host for repo-authority work
  + [manual] is a non-launching human or external worker lane

& [WorkerRecord] is one job in a turn spool
  + [worker_id] is the stable worker folder and tree key
  + [lane] is local_gpu, lm_studio_cli, openai_codex, codex_cli, or manual
  + [objective] is the bounded job objective
  + [prompt_packet] is the prompt or SOP-HG packet sent to the worker
  + [status] is queued, launch_ready, launched, completed, blocked, failed, or deferred
  + [launch_command] is the intended command when launch policy permits
  + [result_file] is the captured output or residual outside note
  + [attention_frame] is optional SOP-HG context for the worker

  = must: every worker has objective, lane, status, and result slot
  = must: launch command is inspectable before execution
  = must: status changes are recorded in the worker file
  = must: capture worker result before the task manager integrates it
  = must: keep codex_cli or current Codex host as the authority layer when local model output may influence repo state
  - never: infer worker completion from process launch alone
